FOOT & MOUTH DISEASE, BOVINE - KAZAKHSTAN (ATYRAU REGION)
*************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Tue 15 May 2007
Source: News Agency "Regnum" [trans. by Assoc.Mod.NP, edited]
<http://www.regnum.ru/news/medicine/827574.html>

FMD detected in animals in Kazakstan
-------------------------------------
FMD [foot and mouth disease] in animals was revealed in the Kzylkoginskiy
district in the Atyrau region of Kazakhstan.
On 15 May 2007 the press service of the Ministry of Emergency Measures of
Kazakhstan reported that FMD had been detected on 14 May 2007 in private
farmsteads including 348 head of cattle, of which 18 animals have been
destroyed and buried. The number of in-contact animals is 1200. The
diagnosis was laboratory-confirmed in the Republic's veterinary laboratory
by testing blood samples. Quarantine measures have been imposed in the
district and control and eradication are being applied.
--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
[Atyrau can be found in western Kazakhstan, on the northern shores of the
Caspian Sea; for an administrative map, go to:
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/commonwealth/kazakhstan_pol01.jpg>.
Further epidemiological data, including the serotype involved, are
expected to be included in the follow-up report to the OIE, due soon.
- Mod.AS].
